This paper deals with information transmission over a noisy channel, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of a feedback channel to improve the decoding error exponent is also a common topic in network information theory (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the reliability function, which is a measure of the probability of error in communication systems, making it relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses mathematical analysis to derive results, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG).
